section.section:
The Treasurer shall provide self-insurance for:
loss of or damage to State motor vehicles;
loss of or damage to hulls of State vessels;
loss of or damage to State real property, to the extent that purchased insurance does not cover the loss or damage; and
loss as a result of a settlement or judgment to the extent that the Board of Public Works pays the loss under Title 12, Subtitle 5 of the State Government Article.
